# Styling and Theme System

## CSS Architecture

- Use CSS custom properties for theming in [styles/color-themes.css](mdc:styles/color-themes.css)
- Global styles in [styles/globals.css](mdc:styles/globals.css)
- Component-specific styles in [styles/mdx-components.css](mdc:styles/mdx-components.css)
- Use Tailwind CSS 4 utility classes for component styling

## Theme System

- Three built-in themes: `minimal`, `minimal-dark`, `mono`
- Use OKLCH color space for better color interpolation
- Define all theme variables in CSS custom properties
- Support for custom themes by adding new CSS classes

## Component Styling

- Use `cn()` utility from [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) for conditional classes
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use semantic color variables: `--primary`, `--foreground`, `--muted`
- Implement proper dark mode support with theme classes

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach with Tailwind breakpoints
- Use `useIsMobile` hook for mobile-specific logic
- Test all components in different screen sizes
- Ensure proper touch targets for mobile devices

## Accessibility

- Use proper ARIA attributes for interactive components
- Ensure sufficient color contrast in all themes
- Support keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML elements
